    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-4010761">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-4010761">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,4010761)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-4010761">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/modernmajorgeneral" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(274283); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=274283&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610163350" alt="ModernMajorGeneral" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=274283)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/modernmajorgeneral" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(274283); return false;" >ModernMajorGeneral</a></span> <span class="odate time_1538475145 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Oct 2018 10:12</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4010761">
									

<p>I don't know if you're Australian, but as an Australian this doesn't feel very Australian to me.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>Oh yeah, how could he forget? Kangaroos were a staple of Australia since the early settlers stepped foot on this country. Without them, many people wouldn’t of given Australia the time of day, let alone even want to settle and create a superpower out of it.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't get what any part of this sentence means. If you're trying to say that foreigners only notice Australia from a tourism/pop culture point of view because of kangaroos, maybe that's an acceptable exaggeration, but nobody <em>lives</em> here because of kangaroos. Unless you're referring to Aborigines (instead of the British) when you say 'early settlers', kangaroos were obviously there before early settlers. And nobody has ever associated 'Australia' with 'superpower' (I found this so odd that it was what captured my attention for the rest of the piece, as I honestly assumed I was going to be reading a weird SCP-universe alternate history where Australia was a superpower).</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Hey, he loved Australia as much as the next boomerang wielding, slogan shouting, barbecuing bogan.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't really get this either. Nobody in Australia describes themselves like this. A foreigner might describe themselves in stereotypes like this, but that confuses the scene-setting function of this line - after reading it, I'm none the wiser whether this is an Australian guy or a foreigner (although if this is an adult Australian guy who drives for a living, there is no way he has never seen a wild kangaroo before).</p>
<p>There are a bunch of things that don't make sense to me. &quot;Maybe Michael could get them to tow his car when they inevitably pass by.&quot; Is this meant to be a sarcastic thought? If not, why would his roadside assistance company 'inevitably' be passing by in the middle of nowhere in the outback? Why is he expecting to be able to pet a kangaroo without it running away? The only people who would do this are foreigners who don't know very much about kangaroos (or drunks), but if he's watched nature documentaries, he knows they're wild animals. How is he driving over animal corpses without noticing them? That's pretty difficult to do.</p>
<p>There are a few other minor inaccuracies/strange details - kangaroos make different noises and I suppose it's not impossible they might squeak or squeal - I don't really know - but it's not how I'd describe kangaroo sounds. (see <a href="https://wildambience.com/wildlife-sounds/kangaroo/">https://wildambience.com/wildlife-sounds/kangaroo/</a> for reference). The rural speed limit is &gt;100km/h in all Australian states. The Australian desert is infamously dry, not humid (usually).</p>
<p>If nothing else, this could use a proofread for spelling/grammar - 'would of', 'that would do to' were errors I noticed, plus some comma use I would disagree with.</p>
<p>Ultimately, though, the tone doesn't work for me. 'Man attacked by horde of angry kangaroos' sounds like something comedic, or that Australians would tell gullible tourists, but here it's played totally straight for horror.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

							</div>

								
